The new wording is mostly careful: it distinguishes the main unified-Qwen official-baseline comparison from the frozen-model substitution check, says the official baselines are held fixed at unified-Qwen values, preserves the Beauty/Movies losses, and avoids upgrading the result to a retuned cross-backbone SOTA claim.

